  <sect1 id="pluma-programming-features">
	  <title lang="en">Programming Features</title>

	  <para lang="en">Several of <application>pluma</application>'s features for programming are provided with plugins. For example, the Tag List plugin provides a list of commonly-used tags for different markup languages: see <xref linkend="pluma-tag-list-plugin"/>.</para>

<!-- ============= Syntax Highlighting =================== -->
	 <sect2 id="pluma-set-highlightmode">
	 <title lang="en">Syntax Highlighting</title>
	 <para lang="en">Syntax highlighting makes source code easier to read by showing different parts of the text in different colors.</para>

	 <para lang="en"><application>pluma</application> chooses an appropriate syntax highlighting mode based on a document's type. To override the syntax highlighting mode, choose <menuchoice> <guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Highlight Mode</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, then choose one of the following menu items:</para>
		  <variablelist>
		    <varlistentry>
		      <term lang="en"><guimenuitem>Normal</guimenuitem></term>
		      <listitem>
		        <para lang="en">Do not display any syntax highlighting.</para>
		      </listitem>
		    </varlistentry>
		    <varlistentry>
		      <term lang="en"><guisubmenu>Sources</guisubmenu></term>
		      <listitem>
		        <para lang="en">Display syntax highlighting to edit source code. Use the <guisubmenu>Sources</guisubmenu> submenu to select the source code type.</para>
		      </listitem>
		    </varlistentry>
		    <varlistentry>
		      <term lang="en"><guisubmenu>Markup</guisubmenu></term>
		      <listitem>
		        <para lang="en">Display syntax highlighting to edit markup code. Use the <guisubmenu>Markup</guisubmenu> submenu to select the markup code type.</para>
		      </listitem>
		    </varlistentry>
		    <varlistentry>
		      <term lang="en"><guisubmenu>Scripts</guisubmenu></term>
		      <listitem>
		        <para lang="en">Display syntax highlighting to edit script code. Use the <guisubmenu>Scripts</guisubmenu> submenu to select the script code type.</para>
		      </listitem>
		    </varlistentry>
		    <varlistentry>
		      <term lang="en"><guisubmenu>Others</guisubmenu></term>
		      <listitem>
		        <para lang="en">Display syntax highlighting to edit other types of code. Use the <guisubmenu>Others</guisubmenu> submenu to select the code type.</para>
		      </listitem>
		    </varlistentry>
		  </variablelist>
	 </sect2>

<!-- ============= To Pipe the Output of a Command to a File ======= -->
	 <sect2 id="pluma-pipe-output">
		<title lang="en">Piping the Output of a Command to a File</title>
		<para lang="en">You can use <application>pluma</application> to pipe the output of a command to a text file. For example, to pipe the output of an <command>ls</command> command to a text file, type <command>ls | pluma</command>, then press <keycap>Return</keycap>.</para>
		<para lang="en">The output of the <command>ls</command> command is displayed in a new text file in the <application>pluma</application> window.</para>
		<para lang="en">Alternatively, you can use the <application>External tools</application> plugin to pipe command output to the current file. <!-- fixme: xref needed! --></para>
	 </sect2>
  </sect1>

